    <h2>Star Rats</h2>
    <p>On December 14, 2021, we released the prologue to the MIT Mystery Hunt, <em>Star Rats</em>. Intended as a introductory puzzle set for the Mystery Hunt proper, we were thrilled at the level of participation we saw.</p>

    <p><em>Star Rats</em> was comprised of 13 puzzles and a metapuzzle.</p>

    <ul>
      <li>186 registered teams solved at least one puzzle.</li>
      <li>Teams solved an average of <strong>9</strong> puzzles before solving the Star Rats metapuzzle.</li>
      <li><strong>Algernon</strong> was the most-solved Star Rats puzzle.</p></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="flourish-embed flourish-chart" data-src="visualisation/8481196"><script src="https://public.flourish.studio/resources/embed.js"></script></div>
    <div class="flourish-embed flourish-chart" data-src="visualisation/8480995"><script src="https://public.flourish.studio/resources/embed.js"></script></div>

    <h2>MIT Mystery Hunt 2022</h2>
    <p>The 2022 MIT Mystery Hunt kicked off at 12 noon TIMEMIT  on Friday January 14 2022. The first round of puzzles unlocked at 1 PM. The hunt remained open until wrap-up at 12 noon, Monday January 17 2022. All statistics below are confined to this timeframe.</p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>393</strong> teams registered.</li>
        <li><strong>303</strong> teams submitted an answer for at least one puzzle.</li>
        <li><strong>279</strong> teams solved at least one puzzle.</li>
        <li><strong>128</strong> teams solved <strong>The Investigation</strong> metapuzzle.</li>
        <li><strong>66</strong> teams solved <strong>The Ministry</strong> metapuzzle.</li>
        <li><strong>60</strong> teams solved <strong>Fruit Around</strong> and earned the New Berry pin.</li>
        <li><strong>48</strong> teams solved at least one <strong>Bookspace</strong> metapuzzle.</li>
        <li><strong>9</strong> teams completed the Hunt.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Of the nine teams who completed the Hunt, these <strong>5</strong> completed it without any hints:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>✈️✈️✈️ Galactic Trendsetters ✈️✈️✈️</li>
      <li>Left Out</li>
      <li>teammate</li>
      <li>Death and Mayhem</li>
      <li>UNICODE EQUIVALENCE</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Below is an animation of the top teams' progress throughout the hunt. We also built an <a href="https://public.flourish.studio/visualisation/8489681/">animation of just the meta solves</a>, which is a slightly more accurate representation of rankings.</p>
